<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJORS; MITCHELL RETURNS TO LINEUP FOR REDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM KAWAKAMI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Outfielder Kevin Mitchell of the Cincinnati Reds, who sat out two games 
because of an eye injury suffered in a bar incident, was back in the lineup 
Monday against the Dodgers. Before the game, Red General Manager Jim Bowden 
issued a statement saying the team had completed its investigation of the 
incident and had cleared Mitchell of any wrongdoing. 
</P>
<P>
 Mitchell suffered a swollen right eye Friday night after being hit at a 
prominent Cincinnati-area nightspot. He sat out the last two weekend games 
against the Colorado Rockies. 
</P>
<P>
 Mitchell told the Reds he was an innocent bystander at The Waterfront, a 
restaurant-bar frequented by athletes, when he was hit by a flying bottle. His 
account was disputed again Monday night by the establishment's owner. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Ruby, the restaurant owner, told the Associated Press on Monday night 
that Mitchell got into a disagreement with a woman he knew and she hit him with 
a beer mug. TIM KAWAKAMI 
</P>
</TEXT>
