<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: LA VALLETTA; SCHOOL FOR SCANDAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Alarm at the incidence of high-level bribery and corruption involving 
governments and big business will be the focus of a biannual conference of 
European and American justice ministries today and Wednesday in La Valletta, 
Malta. 
</P>
<P>
 East European countries such as Bulgaria and Slovakia will be among the 29 
delegations at the conference, organized by the Council of Europe. 
</P>
<P>
 Italy, where a nationwide scandal triggered a voter revolt that toppled a 
long-lived political dynasty, will present the main paper at the conference. 
Four judicial experts led by new Justice Minister Alfredo Biondi make up the 
Italian delegation. The U.S. team includes the Justice Department's Michael 
Defeo. 
</P>
