<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: PARIS; SUMMIT ON AIDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ministers of health from 40 countries will gather in Paris Friday and Saturday 
to discuss the AIDS pandemic and plan a December summit on the crisis.French 
Minister of Health Simon Veil said heads of state will be invited to attend the 
end-of-the-year meeting, which is expected to be the year's top forum on AIDS. 
</P>
<P>
 On the table this week will be topics selected by the World Heatlh 
Organization and the French hosts, including the need for continuing research 
on a vaccine and safeguards for blood-transfusion supplies. France is a major 
center of AIDS research. 
</P>
