<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: HEALTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Merck & Co. Raises Prices on 22 Drugs, Cuts Them on 2: The New Jersey-based 
pharmaceutical company said it raised prices from 2.7% to 3.8% on medications 
such as its ulcer drug Pepcid; Vasotec, its drug for high blood pressure, and 
Proscar, its drug for benign enlarged prostate. Merck cut the prices of two 
cholesterol drugs: the 40-milligram dose of Zocorby, by 32%, and the 
10-milligram dose of Mevacor, by 28%. 
</P>
