<TEXT>
<P>
 Macy, Federated Officials Confer: R.H. Macy & Co. executives, who have opposed 
Federated Department Stores' plan to merge the two retailers, have begun 
meeting with Federated officials to hear details of the proposal, sources 
said.But after their first meeting last Friday, "we still believe our plan 
would offer the most recovery to the creditors," a Macy official said. The 
rival retailers have been trying to win support from Macy creditors for 
competing bankruptcy reorganization plans. Macy's proposal provides for the 
company to return to public ownership under current management. But Federated 
wants creditors to accept a plan that calls for Federated to take over its 
rival. 
