</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As expected, Walt Disney Co. has named publishing executive Michael Lynton 
president of its Hollywood Pictures division. He succeeds Ricardo Mestres, who 
resigned in April. 
</P>
<P>
 Lynton's appointment is unusual because of his lack of background in the film 
business. For the last three years, he has been senior vice president of Disney 
Publishing Group, where he has overseen Disney's domestic publishing 
operations, including Hyperion Books. 
</P>
<P>
 However, Lynton is also a close friend of David Hoberman, Disney's president 
of motion pictures, whom he will report to. Lynton will assume his new post 
June 27. 
</P>
<P>
 * Sony Pictures Entertainment has named Fred Bernstein president of Columbia 
TriStar Motion Picture Cos. As expected, he will team with Columbia TriStar 
Chairman Mark Canton in the management of Sony's motion picture operations.  
</P>
<P>
 * Tom Ruegger has signed a new multiyear deal as executive producer for Warner 
Bros. Animation. 
</P>
<P>
 * SI Communications has appointed Lauren Walker director of radio operations. 
</P>
<P>
 * Janine M. Coughlin has joined Atlantis Films' Santa Monica office as 
director of literary development. 
</P>
<P>
 * Thierry Magon de la Villehuchet, chairman and chief executive of Credit 
Lyonnais Securities U.S.A., is leaving the investment banking firm to pursue 
other activities in finance. 
</P>
<P>
 * Heidi Sinclair has joined the Burson-Marsteller public relations firm in Los 
Angeles as head of its interactive and entertainment technologies practice. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jerry Brown has been promoted to senior account executive for music at Lee 
Solters Co. 
</P>
<P>
 * Adeena Karsseboom has been promoted to vice president of development at 
Raffaella Productions. 
</P>
