<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; REALTORS HONOR POSTERS FOR FAIR HOUSING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For the sixth year in a row, a Simi Valley realtors group is honoring local 
youths who designed posters advocating fair housing. 
</P>
<P>
 The Simi Valley-Moorpark Assn. of Realtors awarded cash prizes of up to $200 
to seven Simi Valley youths whose posters depict the contest's theme of equal 
housing regardless of race, religion, sex, age or disability. 
</P>
<P>
 First-place winners are Simi Valley High School senior Amie Chessen, 17; 
Hillside Junior High School freshman Ryan Cramer, 15, and Pine Crest Elementary 
School sixth-grader Kristin Polanski, 12. 
</P>
<P>
 Amie, who has won first place twice before, said she plans to pursue art 
studies when she graduates from high school this summer. 
</P>
<P>
 "The funny thing is, I'm a procrastinator," said Amie, who created her winning 
entry with oil-based colored pencils in about six hours the night before the 
contest deadline. "The idea just came to me, and it didn't take that long to do 
it." 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan, who created his winning poster using an air brush, plans to teach the 
technique at a Simi Valley arts supply store this summer. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's really cool what you can do with air brush," Ryan said. "I'm still 
experimenting with new ways." 
</P>
<P>
 Kristin said she has already signed up to take Ryan's class. The winning 
posters will be sold by the realtors group in a silent auction. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call education coordinator Maizie Pace at 527-2302, Ext. 
11. SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</TEXT>
