EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; STEREO SHOP OWNER SUSPECT IN ROBBERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Reseda stereo store owner was arrested on suspicion of conspiring to commit 
armed robberies at two stereo equipment stores in Simi Valley and Irvine, Simi 
Valley detectives said Monday . 
</P>
<P>
 Dennis Barish , 35, of Chatsworth posted bail Monday at Ventura County Jail 
and is scheduled to be arraigned in Ventura County Superior Court on Friday, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley Police Detective Tom Marshall said investigators focused on Barish 
as a suspect because he was seen by employees in both stores several days 
before they were robbed in February and May. 
</P>
<P>
 Across the street from Barish's stereo store in Reseda is a U-Haul company 
that loaned out trucks to Barish on the days the robberies occurred, Marshall 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Detectives served search warrants at Barish's house and business on Friday and 
recovered some of the $110,000 worth of stereo equipment stolen from both 
stores. 
</P>
<P>
 Marshall said investigators do not believe Barish was actually involved in the 
robberies that took place Feb. 3 at Hi Fonics Corp. in Simi Valley and on May 
27 at Advanced Marketing and Distributors of Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 Marshall said, "He didn't do the actual robbery. We feel he cased the joints 
and rented the U-Hauls for the robberies." PEGGY Y. LEE 
