ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; WORKER BURNED IN FACTORY FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 42-year-old Garden Grove man suffered facial burns Sunday night when flames 
erupted inside a building where wooden mini-blinds are manufactured. 
</P>
<P>
 Trong Van Dang, an employee of Travis Industries, had second-degree burns to 
the side of his face from the 9:33 p.m. fire and was taken to Anaheim Medical 
