<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; WOMAN RAPED IN HER HOME BY INTRUDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police said they are investigating an early morning rape Monday in the 
Westpark section of the city and the attempted break-in of two nearby houses. 
</P>
<P>
 A 26-year-old woman, who was alone in her home, called police about 7:30 a.m. 
to report that she had been awakened in her second floor bedroom and raped by a 
man who had broken into her home. 
</P>
<P>
 She was being treated at a local hospital, Police Lt. Sam Allevato said. 
</P>
<P>
 The attacker apparently entered the single-family residence by forcing open a 
laundry room window, Allevato said. He ransacked the first floor before 
entering the bedroom. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman told police that the man did not display a weapon during the attack, 
but he threatened her and told her not to call police, Allevato said. 
</P>
<P>
 Two other homes on an adjoining street had signs of attempted forced entry, 
Allevato said. At one of the homes, a garage was entered and a car ransacked. 
</P>
<P>
 Through April of this year, there have been four reported rapes in the city, 
Allevato said. 
</P>
<P>
 There have been no other recent break-ins reported in the Westpark area, he 
said. MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
</TEXT>
