<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: SHERMAN OAKS; SENIOR HOUSING OVER PARKING LOT OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HUGO MARTIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles City Council has approved plans for a two-story apartment 
building for senior citizens to be built on top of a city-owned public parking 
lot on Dickens Street in Sherman Oaks. 
</P>
<P>
 The low-income housing project will cost more than $10 million and include 83 
units over a three-level, 247-space public parking lot. 
</P>
<P>
 Construction is expected to begin by the end of summer and be completed within 
a year, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The project, approved Friday, is expected to create about 70 more parking 
spaces than currently exist on the lot near the corner of Ventura and Van Nuys 
boulevards. 
</P>
<P>
 The federal Department of Housing and Urban Development is funding about $7 
million of the costs, while the city is paying $1 million. The city also is 
providing a $2.5-million loan, which will be paid back before the project is 
completed. HUGO MARTIN 
</P>
</TEXT>
