SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; MAN KILLED WHEN PICKUP FLIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Saugus man died when he lost control of his pickup truck, which overturned 
on a two-lane road, striking a second car whose driver had to be hospitalized, 
a California Highway Patrol official said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Donald Ellis, 59, was pronounced dead at the scene of the accident, which 
occurred about 4:15 p.m. Sunday on Vasquez Canyon Road about one mile east of 
Bouquet Canyon Road, said Officer Wendy Moore.She said Ellis was driving a 1987 
Ford Ranger westbound at an unknown speed when his truck drifted onto the right 
dirt shoulder. 
</P>
<P>
 "He over-corrected and steered back into the westbound lane, and then into the 
eastbound lane," she added. "(Ellis) then swerved to the right, causing (it) to 
overturn." 
</P>
<P>
 The top portion of the truck's cab struck the front hood of an eastbound 1993 
Toyota Corolla driven by Charles Ferguson, 43, of Saugus, Moore said. Ferguson 
was taken to Henry Mayo Newhall Memorial Hospital in Valencia with moderate 
injuries. 
</P>
