<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: COURT RULING A SETBACK FOR NEW IMAGE INDUSTRIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Bay Area federal court, granting a preliminary injunction in a 
patent-infringement lawsuit, has ordered New Image Industries Inc. of Canoga 
Park to stop making, using or selling its dental intra-oral camera. 
</P>
<P>
 The court's order came after High Tech Medical Instrumentation Inc. of Santa 
Rosa filed a lawsuit in November contending that certain features of New 
Image's AcuCam camera infringes a patent held by High Tech.The AcuCam is a 
pen-sized camera that is one of New Image's main products. 
</P>
<P>
 Roger Leddington, New Image's chief executive officer, acknowledged that the 
court's order was a setback. But he said the company on Friday began shipment 
of the AcuCam camera with a redesigned handpiece to avoid the alleged patent 
infringement. At the same time, Leddington said New Image would continue to 
oppose the suit and that it has appealed the court's order. 
</P>
