<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: CALIFORNIA AMPLIFIER REPORTS DROP IN EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 California Amplifier Inc., a Camarillo maker of components used in the 
distribution of television signals, said its earnings fell 25% on a 30% rise in 
revenues in the first quarter, which ended May 28. 
</P>
<P>
 In the latest quarter, profits were $406,000, compared to $540,000 in the 
previous year. First-quarter revenues rose to $11.2 million, from $8.6 million 
in the same period a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 The company attributed the results to price competition in the market for 
satellite television products and increased spending for research and 
development. 
</P>
