<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: DEVELOPMENT-STAGE FIRM AVCON TO GO PUBLIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Avcon Inc., an Agoura Hills producer of magnetic fields that serve as 
bearings, said it has filed a registration statement with the Securities and 
Exchange Commission for an initial public offering of 1 million shares of 
common stock worth about $8.25 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Proceeds from the public offering will be used to establish a manufacturing 
plant to mass-produce the devices, which suspend rotating shafts in magnetic 
fields rather than on lubricated bearings.Until now, the company's business has 
been the research and development of a few dozen custom-made prototypes for 
customers who may use them in various industrial pumps. Reynders, Gray Co. Inc. 
of New York will act as underwriters. 
</P>
<P>
 Avcon reported net income of $72,047 on revenue of $1.3 million in 1993. 
</P>
