<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: MICROPOLIS EXPECTS LARGER 2ND-QUARTER LOSS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Micropolis Corp., a Chatsworth maker of computer disk drives and other 
products, said it expects its net loss from operations for the quarter ending 
July 1 to be "significantly larger" than in its first quarter ended April 1, 
when it had a net loss of $9.76 million. 
</P>
<P>
 The company declined to state a reason for the larger loss, other than to say 
that its second-quarter revenue and profit margins would shrink. It said that 
its cash position would be reduced to $72 million as of July 1 from $82 million 
on April 1. 
</P>
<P>
 Micropolis also said it expects its operating loss in its third quarter will 
be greater than the approximately $4.5 million that analysts have projected. 
</P>
