<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: SALES UP, PRICES DOWN FOR HOMES IN SIMI, MOORPARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sales of existing single-family houses in Simi Valley, Moorpark and Santa Rosa 
edged up 2% in April from a year earlier, but the average price dropped 5%. 
</P>
<P>
 The Simi Valley-Moorpark Assn. of Realtors said 161 single-family houses 
changed hands in April, up from 131 in March and 158 in April, 1993. But the 
average price of a single-family house that was sold in April, 1994, was 
$210,586, down from $220,591 a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 Condominium sales in the Simi Valley and Moorpark area were flat in April, as 
18 condos closed escrow. In April the average sale price of condos fell 4%, to 
$130,179 from $135,492 a year earlier, the realty group said. 
</P>
