<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW: ROCKWELL EXTENDS PACT WITH VENTURA FIRM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A contract renewal from industrial giant Rockwell International Corp. will 
allow a small Ventura firm, 1st Step Industrial & Filter Inc., to double its 
revenues in the coming year, the company says. 
</P>
<P>
 1st Step, which is owned and managed by three women, markets industrial 
filters for two leaders in that field, American Air Filter and Norgren 
Compressed Air Filter. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ventura company has just won an extension through 1999 of a deal for 
Rockwell to use American Air and Norgren filters to clear the air at Rockwell 
installations worldwide. Rockwell also agreed to expand its use of the devices. 
</P>
<P>
 "Our revenues totaled $1 million last year and, as a result of this contract, 
we expect that figure to double," said Shelene Robinson, 1st Step's sales 
manager and one of its owners. "And it could go much higher than that a few 
years from now." 
</P>
<P>
 Robinson credits government and company policies favoring women-owned and 
small concerns with helping the firm land the contract. 
</P>
</TEXT>
