<TEXT>
<P>
 Disney Chief Vows Tenacity on Virginia Park: Walt Disney Co. Chairman Michael 
D. Eisner said he has been surprised by the strong opposition to the company's 
proposed theme park in Virginia but said he has no intention of dropping the 
project."If the people think we will back off, they are mistaken," Eisner told 
the Washington Post. Eisner said he wants to make the completion of Disney's 
America, a $650-million theme park focused on U.S. history, the highlight of 
his chairmanship. 
</P>
