</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Caesars World Inc. Expects Lower Profit: The Los Angeles-based company 
predicted a "substantial reduction" in net income for the fourth quarter ending 
July 31 compared to the same quarter a year ago, when it was $25,686,000, or 
$1.04 a share. The company attributed the decline to "recent unusually large 
losses to a small number of long-term table game customers" in Nevada. The 
company estimated the losses to those customers at more than $18 million. 
</P>
