<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS ROUNDUP: COMPANY TOWN; GEFFEN PLANS VIDEO 'JIGSAW' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Geffen Records said Monday that it will release the "Vid Grid" CD-ROM game in 
which players piece together parts of music videos like a jigsaw puzzle. 
</P>
<P>
 The West Hollywood-based label, a unit of Japan's Matsushita Electric 
Industrial Co., said the game, which it developed with Jasmine Multimedia 
Publishing Inc. of Van Nuys, will be available in September. 
</P>
<P>
 The game features nine music videos from Geffen acts Aerosmith, Peter Gabriel 
and Guns N' Roses, as well as artists from competing labels such as 
Soundgarden, the Red Hot Chili Peppers and Metallica, a statement said. 
</P>
