<P>
 Denmark Bound: The Burlington Air Express name is headed for Denmark. 
</P>
<P>
 The Irvine-based freight forwarder has signed a deal that will result in Inter 
Express, a Copenhagen-based freight firm, using the Burlington name and 
handling the network's Danish freight. 
</P>
<P>
 "Burlington seeks out high-profile, service-oriented companies to join its 
global network of over 490 offices," said Ray Wilson, Burlington's chief 
